---
import WebLayout from '../layouts/WebLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<WebLayout title="Gold Shore | Designed to Steer Capital" description="Designed not to manage capital, but to steer it.">
  <section class="gs-hero gs-blueprint-bg" data-gs-hero>
    <canvas class="gs-webgl-field" data-gs-webgl aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
    <div class="gs-css-field" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="gs-stars-deep" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="gs-stars" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="gs-grid-overlay" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="gs-vignette" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="gs-hero-parallax" data-gs-parallax="1.2" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="gs-container gs-hero-content gs-seq gs-vt">
      <div class="gs-kicker gs-signal gs-i-0" data-gs-reveal>System Status: Operational</div>
      <h1 class="gs-hero-title gs-display gs-i-1" data-gs-reveal>Designed Not to Manage Capital, but to Steer It.</h1>
      <p class="gs-i-2" data-gs-reveal>
        Gold Shore delivers institutional-grade infrastructure, automation systems, and operational intelligence
        designed for scale, resilience, and deterministic control.
      </p>

      <div class="gs-hero-actions gs-i-3" data-gs-reveal>
        <a class="gs-button gs-button-solid" href="/services">View Services</a>
        <a class="gs-button gs-button-outline" href="/developer">Developer Access</a>
        <button class="gs-button gs-button-outline" data-gs-modal-open="subscribe">Request Brief</button>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-signal-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <div style="margin-top: 2rem; display:grid; gap: 1rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));">
        <div class="gs-panel gs-hoverlift" data-gs-reveal>
          <div class="gs-label">Availability</div>
          <div style="font-size:2.2rem; font-weight:700; margin-top:0.4rem;">99.995%</div>
          <div class="gs-micro gs-muted">Measured across distributed surfaces</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gs-panel gs-hoverlift" data-gs-reveal>
          <div class="gs-label">Deployment Cadence</div>
          <div style="font-size:2.2rem; font-weight:700; margin-top:0.4rem;">Continuous</div>
          <div class="gs-micro gs-muted">Guarded promotion paths</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gs-panel gs-hoverlift" data-gs-reveal>
          <div class="gs-label">Signal Throughput</div>
          <div style="font-size:2.2rem; font-weight:700; margin-top:0.4rem;">2.1B / Day</div>
          <div class="gs-micro gs-muted">Routed and validated events</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="gs-angle-divider"></div>

  <section class="gs-section">
    <div class="gs-container">
      <h2 class="gs-display" data-gs-reveal>Institutional Infrastructure</h2>
      <p data-gs-reveal>
        Modern systems do not fail because of lack of ambition — they fail because of uncontrolled complexity.
      </p>
      <p data-gs-reveal>
        Gold Shore architects resilient platforms engineered for deterministic deployment pipelines, high-availability
        surface management, controlled access hierarchies, observability-first operations, and real-time signal
        ingestion with enrichment.
      </p>
      <p data-gs-reveal>We design systems that remain stable under volatility, load, and regulatory pressure.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="gs-section">
    <div class="gs-container">
      <h2 class="gs-display" data-gs-reveal>Operating Model</h2>
      <p data-gs-reveal>
        We operate with infrastructure-as-code discipline, typed service boundaries, controlled blast-radius
        deployments, and observability pipelines spanning metrics, tracing, and structured logs.
      </p>
      <p data-gs-reveal>
        Multi-environment promotion governance is enforced at every layer. Gold Shore is built for operators — not
        spectators.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</WebLayout>

<style>
  .gs-hero-parallax {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(90, 140, 255, 0.08), transparent 55%);
    mix-blend-mode: screen;
  }
</style>
